race.comment: LEGACY BAY (1) has run out of track over 1100m and 1200m in two goes this prep. Both races have rated well and she has shaped as well as any. Now she gets to 1400m around the Lakeside which was the stage for her peak and win last campaign and she can repeat the feat this time around. STAGE 'N' SCREEN (2) has a similar look in the form book. Placed in both spins this time and with past ratings that jump off the page a bit. COLOUR OUR WORLD (6) will have to do more to follow up the Warrnambool win but she has been better over further than 1200m in the past which paints the fresh win in a nice light. DIVINE JUSTICE (14) was hard to miss first up and with improvement to come second up, she holds solid claims.
